This is a bad position for the queen to be moved to.  It allows black to develop his WSB and forces the queen to be moved again.  One of the goals of an opening is to develop your pieces without moving the same one multiple times.  Here the queen has already moved twice and will be forced to move a third.  White would have been better with Bb5, both developing another piece and pinning the knight.
